<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy | Sealient Apps</title>

  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f0f4f8;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .section-header {
      border-bottom: 2px solid #3b82f6;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      margin-top: 1.8rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body class="p-4 sm:p-8 md:p-12 lg:p-16">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-2xl rounded-xl p-6 md:p-12 border border-gray-200">

    <header class="mb-8 border-b pb-4">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-blue-700">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mt-2">
        Applicable to:
        <span id="app-name-placeholder" class="font-bold text-blue-500">Sealient Apps</span>
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-1">
        Effective Date: June 27, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="text-gray-700">

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">1. Introduction</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Sealient</strong> ("we", "us", or "our")
        collects, uses, stores, protects, and shares information when you use our mobile
        applications, websites, products, and related services, including
        <strong><span id="app-name-placeholder-2">Sealient Apps</span></strong>.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        By using our applications or services, you agree to the practices described in this
        Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use our
        applications or services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">2. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 text-gray-700">2.1 Personal Information</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We do not intentionally collect personally identifiable information such as your name,
        email address, phone number, home address, or payment information unless you voluntarily
        provide it to us, such as when you contact us for support.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 text-gray-700">2.2 Device and Usage Information</h3>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Some of our applications may collect limited technical and usage information to improve
        performance, reliability, security, and user experience. This may include:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Device model and manufacturer</li>
        <li>Operating system version</li>
        <li>App version</li>
        <li>Language and region settings</li>
        <li>Crash logs and diagnostic data</li>
        <li>Performance data</li>
        <li>General app usage statistics</li>
        <li>Anonymous identifiers, such as app instance ID or advertising ID</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 text-gray-700">2.3 User Content</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Some applications may process content or data that you choose to provide in order to
        perform requested features. Such processing is limited to the functionality of the
        application.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        Whenever possible, user content is processed locally on your device. We do not upload,
        store, sell, or share your personal content unless a specific feature clearly requires it
        and informs you beforehand.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">3. App Permissions</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Depending on the features of a particular application, our apps may request certain
        permissions, including but not limited to:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Camera access</li>
        <li>Photos, media, or file access</li>
        <li>Microphone access</li>
        <li>Notification permission</li>
        <li>Internet access</li>
        <li>Location access</li>
        <li>Bluetooth or nearby device access</li>
        <li>Calendar access</li>
        <li>Contacts access</li>
        <li>Storage access</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mb-4">
        Permissions are requested only when needed for app functionality. You can disable
        permissions at any time through your device settings, although some features may not work
        properly without the required permissions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">4. Advertising</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Some of our applications may display advertisements. Advertising partners may collect or
        receive limited information such as advertising ID, device information, approximate
        location, ad interactions, and usage data to provide, measure, and improve ads.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        You may be able to reset or limit the use of your advertising ID through your device
        settings.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">5. Analytics and Crash Reporting</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We may use analytics and crash reporting tools to understand how our applications are used,
        detect errors, improve performance, and enhance user experience. These tools may collect
        technical information such as app usage, device information, crash logs, and diagnostic data.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">6. Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Some applications may offer in-app purchases or subscriptions. Payments are processed by
        app stores or payment providers. We do not directly collect or store your full payment card
        information.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        Purchase status, subscription status, product identifiers, and transaction-related
        information may be used to provide paid features and manage access to premium content.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">7. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Our applications may integrate third-party services such as analytics, crash reporting,
        advertising, cloud services, authentication, payment processing, or other infrastructure
        providers.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        These third-party services may collect information according to their own privacy policies.
        We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party services used within
        our applications.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">8. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We do not sell your personal information. We may share limited information with
        third-party service providers only when necessary to operate, analyze, improve, secure,
        or monetize our applications, or when required by law.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        We may also share aggregated or anonymized information that cannot reasonably be used to
        identify you.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">9. Data Retention</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We retain information only for as long as necessary to provide our services, improve our
        applications, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-4">
        User content processed locally on your device remains under your control and may be deleted
        by deleting the content or uninstalling the application.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">10. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Information processed by us or by third-party service providers may be transferred to and
        processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have data
        protection laws that differ from those in your location.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">11. Data Security</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect information from
        unauthorized access, loss, misuse, alteration, or disclosure. However, no method of
        transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">12. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Our applications are not intended to knowingly collect personal information from children
        under the age required by applicable law. If you believe that a child has provided personal
        information to us, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps to remove such
        information.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">13. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        Depending on your location and applicable laws, you may have certain rights regarding your
        information, including:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>The right to access information we may hold about you</li>
        <li>The right to request correction or deletion of your information</li>
        <li>The right to withdraw permissions through your device settings</li>
        <li>The right to opt out of certain advertising or analytics practices where available</li>
        <li>The right to contact us regarding privacy-related concerns</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mb-4">
        To exercise your rights, please contact us using the email address provided below.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">14. Compliance</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This Privacy Policy is intended to comply with applicable privacy laws and platform
        requirements, including Google Play Developer Policies, GDPR, CCPA, and other applicable
        data protection laws where relevant.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">15. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this
        page with an updated effective date. Your continued use of our applications after changes
        are posted means that you accept the updated Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 section-header">16. Contact Us</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        If you have any questions, requests, or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy
        practices, please contact us:
      </p>

      <p class="font-semibold text-blue-600">
        Developer: Sealient
        <br />
        Email:
        <a href="mailto:sealientsupport@gmail.com" aria-label="Email Sealient Support">
          sealientsupport@gmail.com
        </a>
      </p>

    </section>

    <footer class="mt-10 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300 text-sm text-center text-gray-500">
      <p>
        &copy; 2026 <span id="store-name-placeholder-footer">Sealient</span>.
        All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </footer>

  </div>

  <script>
    function getQueryParams() {
      const params = {};
      const queryString = window.location.search.substring(1);

      if (!queryString) {
        return params;
      }

      const pairs = queryString.split('&');

      pairs.forEach(pair => {
        const [key, value] = pair.split('=');

        if (key && value) {
          params[decodeURIComponent(key).trim()] = decodeURIComponent(value).trim();
        }
      });

      return params;
    }

    function updatePolicyContent() {
      const params = getQueryParams();

      const defaultAppName = "Sealient Apps";
      const appName = params.app || defaultAppName;

      document.title = "Privacy Policy | " + appName;

      const appNamePlaceholders = document.querySelectorAll(
        '#app-name-placeholder, #app-name-placeholder-2'
      );

      appNamePlaceholders.forEach(element => {
        element.textContent = appName;
      });
    }

    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', updatePolicyContent);
  </script>
</body>
</html>